The paper deals with graph theory and specifically focuses on the concept of linear rank-width, which is a measure of the complexity of a graph. This makes cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) the most likely categories. The paper also involves the study of graph decompositions and characterizations, which falls under cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper provides algorithms and computational results, which could also make it relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
